### [Proverbs Chapter 16](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#001.md)

[Proverbs 16:1](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">pro 16:1</span></span>

From the Lord - Men can neither think nor speak wisely and well without
Divine assistance.

[Proverbs 16:2](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#002.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_002">pro 16:2</span></span>

Weigheth - Exactly knows as men do the things which they weigh. Spirits
- The hearts of men.

[Proverbs 16:3](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">pro 16:3</span></span>

Commit - Refer all thy actions and concerns to God, as the end of them,
and depend upon God's providence for success. Established - Thy designs
shall be brought to an happy issue.

[Proverbs 16:4](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">pro 16:4</span></span>

Doth work - He orders or disposes. For - For his own glory; for the
discovery of his wisdom, power, goodness, truth, justice. The wicked -
Wilful and impenitent sinners. Men make themselves wicked, and God
therefore makes them miserable.

[Proverbs 16:6](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#006.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_006">pro 16:6</span></span>

By mercy - By a merciful and just and faithful frame of heart and course
of life. Is purged - As they qualify a man to offer up acceptable
prayers to God for the pardon of his sins. By fear - By a filial
reverence unto God. Depart - They are kept from abusing pardoning mercy,
and from returning to folly or wickedness.

[Proverbs 16:9](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#009.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_009">pro 16:9</span></span>

Deviseth - Proposes what he will do. Directeth - Over - rules and
disposes all his designs and actions.

[Proverbs 16:10](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#010.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_010">pro 16:10</span></span>

A divine sentence - Great sagacity and piercing judgment. Of the king -
Of wise kings; who only are worthy of that name and office.

[Proverbs 16:11](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#011.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_011">pro 16:11</span></span>

The Lord's - Are made by his direction and appointment, so that no man
can alter them without violating God's rights and authority.

[Proverbs 16:15](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#015.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_015">pro 16:15</span></span>

A cloud - As acceptable as those clouds which bring the latter rain,
whereby the fruits are filled and ripened a little before the harvest.

[Proverbs 16:17](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#017.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_017">pro 16:17</span></span>

The high - way - Their common road, in which they walk, tho' through
frailty or temptation they slip into the bypath of sin. From evil - From
the evil of sin, and consequently from the evil of punishment. Keepeth -
That takes heed to walk in that high - way.

[Proverbs 16:20](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#020.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_020">pro 16:20</span></span>

Good - He who orders his affairs with discretion.

[Proverbs 16:21](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#021.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_021">pro 16:21</span></span>

The wise - He who is truly wise, shall be so accounted by others.
Sweetness - Eloquence added to wisdom. Increaseth - Both in himself, for
while a man teaches others, he improves himself; and others, who by this
means are induced to hear and receive his instructions.

[Proverbs 16:22](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#022.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_022">pro 16:22</span></span>

The instruction - Their most grave and serious counsels are foolish.

[Proverbs 16:23](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#023.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_023">pro 16:23</span></span>

Teacheth - Directs him what to speak, and keeps him from speaking
foolishly. Addeth - Enables him to speak learnedly and wisely.

[Proverbs 16:27](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#027.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_027">pro 16:27</span></span>

Diggeth up - Prosecutes his evil designs with great industry. His lips -
His tongue is set on fire of hell.

[Proverbs 16:30](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#030.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_030">pro 16:30</span></span>

Shutteth - That his thoughts may be more intent. Moving - Which is the
gesture of one whose thoughts are deeply engaged.

[Proverbs 16:32](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#032.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_032">pro 16:32</span></span>

Is better - Of a more gallant and generous spirit, and more valiant and
victorious.

[Proverbs 16:33](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#033.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_033">pro 16:33</span></span>

The lot - As the ancient practice was in deciding doubtful things. The
event of which though casual to men, is directed by God's providence.

